rComments: Terrible prof, avoid her if you can. Oftentimes no explanation would be better than the nonsensical slides she blasts through. Grading criteria made no sense. Don't expect to learn anything from the lectures or from her, just study slides and meet with the TA as often as possible. Doable, but needlessly frustrating. Also quite rude to students.

Good teacher, stat with her very easy and interesting. she is laid back, don't stress students with a lot of homeworks or readings. Bonus marks just for attendance, and more bonus for optional assignment. I highly recommend her.
Disorganized. Changes her mind after responding to your e-mails. Lectures are dry and long, good thing the course has a good TA!

She is a really good prof. Statistics is hard, but she has a laid back approach that eases my anxiety and makes it easier to approach the material. Her exams are really fair, and she wants to see students do well, as long as they make the effort. She is very nice and approachable. I definitely recommend her if you have to take stats.

k... statistics is a tough course to teach, there's a lot of "alternatives" to doing stuff... Kate's course requires A LOT of studying... and it's true, her slides don't really cover the stuff on the exams.. you really just kinda have to do it on your own. But-- if your ok with doing that, her exams aren't tough.

Doesn't know her stuff, dilutes the material. A gazillion slides every lecture, and none of this stuff even shows up on the exam! Her exams are tricky, and don't refer to any of the material done in the class. You'll think you know your stuff, but then you'll go to the exam, and find out otherwise. Strongly recommended you avoid this one. Hate her.

Classes are hard to follow, but i don't think most people can understand stats from just listening.  Kate is always available to meet with students.  She has labs set up, and there are over 6 hours a week for office hours if people need.

OMG. All I can say is I feel for you if you have her as a prof and just get out. Hopefully you'll get someone else...anyone else. I'm going to fail! She is not helpful the text sux. Things HAVE to be done her way but good luck finding out what that was is...
Be prepared to learn the material on your own. Dont bother participating in class and dont expect any help.

I was really excited to take this course and really disappointed with it overall.  The material was easy enough but the professor is very picky about having it done her way and very unclear as to what her way is, thus, making it not so easy at all.  Overall, I feel like the class was way below standards.

This teacher is terrible, I cannot believe she is still teaching. Be careful she is extremely vengeful if she thinks your out of line. She is very biased towards certain students. Although this teacher seems to like me, I would not recommend her to anyone. Her lectures are boring are also boring and her notes are full of mistakes. Stay away!

she is a horrible prof and couldn't teach to save her life.  her exams have questions that were not taught and are not in the textbook.  if you ask her to explain something inadequately explained she'll say "it's what i just said it was".  she overloads you with huge assignments that are worth like nothing (120 hours work for 30%, not cool). >:(

Not the easiest class and she doesn't make the material any easier. If you don't answer she thinks you're stupid but if you do answer and its not perfect you're stupid too. No win situation. She seems nice enough but has long lectures that didn't always make sense.

She didn't quit the class, she got sick and had to leave! As a result I didn't see much of her, but it seems like she'd be good. She was very thorough in the few lectures I had with her. Knows her stuff quite well.
Quit our class halfway through. Doesn't explain her notes. Her notes also have 1092019 mistakes in them. Not recommended. I'm gonna fail.
